ðŸ“Œ Problem Statement
Urban drivers often struggle with finding parking spaces, resulting in traffic congestion, wasted time, and increased fuel consumption. Current systems lack real-time availability, intelligent routing, and a seamless user experience.
ParkiFy tackles this issue with a smart, user-centered platform that guides drivers to available parking spots effortlessly using real-time data and intuitive design.
________________________________________
ðŸ“ Description
ParkiFy is a smart parking solution that:
â€¢	Offers real-time availability of parking spaces
â€¢	Uses data-driven recommendations for nearby slots
â€¢	Provides a user-friendly mobile/web interface
â€¢	Minimizes traffic by guiding users efficiently
â€¢	Enables contactless entry and exit for parking lots
________________________________________
ðŸ“– Abstract
This report presents the application of Design Thinking in developing ParkiFy, a next-gen smart parking platform. By adopting the five stagesâ€”Empathize, Define, Ideate, Prototype, and Testâ€”ParkiFy addresses real-world urban parking challenges and streamlines the experience for both drivers and facility managers.
Through each phase, the platform was shaped using feedback, real user insights, and iterative improvements to ensure it remains functional, scalable, and easy to use.
________________________________________
ðŸ” Introduction
Design Thinking is a human-centric problem-solving approach that focuses on empathy, rapid prototyping, and iterative testing. It was the ideal methodology for ParkiFy due to the following reasons:
â€¢	ðŸš˜ Focus on solving real-world parking challenges faced by everyday users
â€¢	âš™ï¸ Rapid development of MVPs (Minimum Viable Products) for faster feedback
â€¢	ðŸ” Continuous improvement driven by real-time user data and suggestions
â€¢	ðŸ§  Bridge between user needs and technology like IoT, sensors, and smart algorithms



















