Phase 3: Ideate
3.1 Ideation Techniques Employed
3.1.1 Divergent Thinking Sessions
We encouraged creative idea generation through several methods:
â€¢	Brainstorming: Generated 15+ smart parking features without filtering ideas
â€¢	Crazy Eights: Quickly sketched eight interface/feature concepts in 8 minutes
â€¢	Mind Mapping: Mapped out all possible user needs like availability, price, security
â€¢	Reverse Thinking: Imagined the worst parking appâ€”no real-time updates, confusing maps, no supportâ€”to clarify what to avoid
________________________________________
3.1.2 Convergent Thinking Methods
We used structured tools to refine and select the best ideas:
â€¢	Affinity Diagrams: Grouped features by user needsâ€”commuter-focused, owner-focused, navigation, safety, etc.
â€¢	Impact-Effort Matrix: Mapped each idea to effort vs. potential impact
â€¢	Dot Voting: Team voted on highest-value features
â€¢	Feature Prioritization Framework (MoSCoW):
o	Must-Have: Real-time spot updates, navigation, user login
o	Should-Have: Admin dashboard, pricing transparency
o	Could-Have: AI-based predictions, gamification
o	Wonâ€™t-Have (for now): Smart contracts for parking rental
________________________________________
3.2 Innovative Concepts Generated
